"title": "5245: captain",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5245: captain",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A senior military officer, usually in charge of a ruler's personal guards or bodyguards, the temple guard or a group of soldiers. The word is also used to refer to the commander of a ship's crew.</p>\n<h2>Captains in charge of a ruler's personal guards or bodyguards</h2>\n<h3>Potiphar, captain of Pharaoh's guard</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:36\">GEN 37:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen39:1\">GEN 39:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen40:3-Gen40:4\">GEN 40:3–40:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:10\">GEN 41:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:12\">GEN 41:12</a></p>\n<h3>David, captain of Saul's bodyguard</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam22:14\">1SA 22:14</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The captain of the guard arrests Jeremiah</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer37:13\">JER 37:13</a></p>\n<h2>Captains in charge of the temple guard</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:1\">ACT 4:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:24\">ACT 5:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:26\">ACT 5:26</a></p>\n<h2>Captains in charge of soldiers</h2>\n<h3>King Ahaziah sends a captain with fifty men to Elijah</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs1:9-2Kgs1:14\">2KI 1:9–1:14</a></p>\n<h3>Captains come to the help of Deborah</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:14\">JDG 5:14</a></p>\n<h3>Solomon's captains were Israelites</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:22\">1KI 9:22</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr8:9\">2CH 8:9</a></p>\n<h3>God will remove captains in judgment</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:1-Isa3:3\">ISA 3:1–3:3</a></p>\n<h2>Captains in charge of a ship's crew</h2>\n<h3>The ship's captain orders Jonah to call on his god</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:6\">JON 1:6</a></p>\n<h3>Sea captains will bemoan the fall of Babylon</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:17-Rev18:19\">REV 18:17–18:19</a></p>",
